{
  "texts": [
    "It involves changes in volume and length and is categorized based on its timing and causes.",
    "The main types of shrinkage include chemical, autogenous, drying, carbonation, and plastic shrinkage.",
    "The distinction between drying and autogenous shrinkage lies in their mechanisms: drying shrinkage occurs during the hardening process due to moisture loss, causing volumetric changes, while autogenous shrinkage is caused by self-desiccation within the material.",
    "Resistance to drying shrinkage is a crucial factor in ensuring the long-term durability of concrete [25].",
    "Several studies have investigated the behavior of shrinkage."
  ]
}